🏁 Docker Validation Checklist
1. Stop your local backend/frontend
Ctrl + C

No npm run dev should be running.

2. Stop local PostgreSQL
sudo systemctl stop postgresql

Verify:

sudo systemctl status postgresql

Expected:

inactive (dead)
3. Update .env

For Docker:

DB_HOST=postgres
DB_PORT=5432
DB_USER=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=postgres123
DB_NAME=cloudtask
JWT_SECRET=cloudtask_super_secret_key_2026
PORT=5000
4. Check port 5432
sudo lsof -i :5432

Expected:

(no output)

If you still see a process:

sudo kill -9 <PID>
5. Go to Docker directory
cd infrastructure/docker
6. Stop old containers
docker compose down -v
7. Build everything again
docker compose up --build

Wait until you see:

Database Connected
Server running
8. Check containers
docker compose ps

Expected:

cloudtask-postgres
cloudtask-backend
cloudtask-frontend

All Up.

9. Test

Open:

http://localhost:5173

Test:

✅ Register
✅ Login
✅ Dashboard
✅ Add Task
✅ Complete Task
✅ Delete Task
10. Stop Docker
Ctrl + C

or

docker compose down
🔄 Switch Back to Local Development

If you want to use npm run dev again:

Start PostgreSQL
sudo systemctl start postgresql
Change .env
DB_HOST=localhost

Then:

npm run dev